  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge script CounterScript\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nIf the nonce is not corrected through `prank`, `broadcast` or `getNonce`, the next selected fork will do it even though it shouldn't. It's only necessary when called externally (and thus increments the sender nonce).\r\n\r\nShould pass but fails:\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: Unlicense\r\npragma solidity >=0.8.0;\r\n\r\nimport \"ds-test/test.sol\";\r\nimport \"../cheats/Cheats.sol\";\r\n\r\n// https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/3223\r\ncontract Issue3223Test is DSTest {\r\n    Cheats constant vm = Cheats(HEVM_ADDRESS);\r\n    uint256 fork1;\r\n    uint256 fork2;\r\n\r\n    function setUp() public {\r\n        fork1 = vm.createFork(\r\n            \"https://goerli.infura.io/v3/9aa3d95b3bc440fa88ea12eaa4456161\",\r\n            7475589\r\n        );\r\n        fork2 = vm.createFork(\r\n            \"https://api.avax-test.network/ext/bc/C/rpc\",\r\n            12880747\r\n        );\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function testForkNonce() public {\r\n        address user = address(0xF0959944122fb1ed4CfaBA645eA06EED30427BAA);\r\n        assertEq(user, msg.sender);\r\n\r\n       // cheatcode state is passed, but we never corrected the nonce\r\n\r\n        vm.selectFork(fork2);\r\n        assertEq(vm.getNonce(user), 3); // corrects the nonce to 2, even though its not necessary\r\n        vm.prank(user); \r\n        new Counter(); // fails since nonce 2 has been used already\r\n\r\n        vm.selectFork(fork1);\r\n        assertEq(vm.getNonce(user), 3);\r\n        vm.prank(user);\r\n        new Counter();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract Counter {}\r\n```",
